IGNORE-LINES: lines beginning with # are comments
Instructions for Generative AI model in double square brackets should not be communicated to users. Eg: [[Do this but don't print it.]]

#PersonalPortfolioWebsiteIntakeForm.html — a complete, standalone HTML file ready to embed in your website.

[[I'd like a college graduate intake form with the following specifications.  The goal of these instructions 
    is to help a job hunter build an impactful portfolio website as quickly, cheaply and easily as possible, minimizing 
    the user's expenditure of time, money, and energy while remaining true to their actual profile and molding the content. So we 
    want to gather as much pre-existing information as is available and leverage AI as much as possible.]]

Page 1: Basic Information [[single column, mobile responsive]]
Name (required)
Email (required)
Phone [pretty formatted without any comment]
Major [[short text input, not dropdown]]
Specialization 
LinkedIn URL [[For employer reference]]
Buttons: Reset (must be double-clicked), Next

Page 2: Optional Portfolio Resources---Upload or paste pre-existing resume(s), templates, examples and/or components to be used as models for content, layout and/or style.
[[Avoid giving user redundant instructions.]]
* Upload Files such as Resume or LinkedIn profile: PDF, DOC, DOCX; Images; Videos; HTML, Markdown, Text.
    Show two adjacent boxes: the first is the upload button, the second is a long text box for the user to describe how they want the Content box to be used.
    Tip to user: Learn how to download a PDF of your LinkedIn profile. [[Make a link from "download a PDF of your LinkedIn profile" to a pop-up containing pretty-fied version of HumanInstructionsForPrintingLinkedInProfile.md]]
    [[Allow user to upload files]]

* Website addresses (public URLs only): First box is short text; 2nd adjacent box is for the user to describe how they want the Content box to be used.

* Text: For each entry below, show four adjacent boxes: the first for the file type (HTML, Markdown, or raw); 
   the second for the section type, which is a dropdown box listing potential sections based on "Portfolio Section Types.txt." Put a star on the most highly recommended ones (according to AI). 
      Use AI to suggest additional types, if warranted, based on all preceding information. Last of all include "Other" and "None".
   the third a long text box labelled "Content", and 
   the fourth a long text box for the user to describe how they want the Content box to be used.
   
A checkbox labeled "I have the copyright or written permission to use these resources, or I only want to use it as inspiration; please generate something different enough to avoid copyright infringement."
Buttons at both top and bottom: Back, Reset (must be double-clicked), Next

Page 3: Color scheme
    Embed color-theme.html
    Allow user to choose one of above color themes by number or else enter the color codes in hex:
      1. Primary
      2. Secondary
      3. Accent
      4. Dark
      5. Light

Buttons at both top and bottom: Back, Reset (must be double-clicked), Next

Page 4:
  Desired Position
  Job Position Ad [[long text]]
  Buttons at both top and bottom: Reset (must be double-clicked), Back, Submit

[[Form Features
    Progress bar showing each step progression
    Form validation (lenient for optional fields; Name required on page 1)
    All form data collected and logged to console on submission
    Success message displayed on submit

Upon submission of form, write a summary of entire form to MyPersonalPortfolioWebsiteSummary.html

